subsection.def:
record production certificate
                    (紀錄製備證明書), in relation to a specified record,
                means a certificate that certifies the circumstances in which the record was
                produced and that is—(a)in a form specified by the Commissioner;(b)signed by a person authorized in that behalf by the Commissioner;
                        and(c)in the same document containing the record or in another
                        document;

specified record (指明紀錄), in relation to a facilities-related matter, means a record, in a
